President Muhammadu Buhari, Tuesday evening, hosted the Ooni of Ife, Imperial Majesty, Oba Adeyeye Ogunwusi, Ojaja II, in his official residence in the State House, Abuja.  The royal father was said to have arrived the Aso Rock Presidential Villa at about 8.30pm for the meeting. Although details of the meeting and their discussions were not made available by official sources in the State House, The Nation gathered that the royal visitor was on a ‘thank you’ visit to the President. It was also believed that the meeting would have touched on several other social/security issues affecting the country.  Photographs released by President Buhari’s Special Adviser on Media and Publicity, Femi Adesina on his Facebook page in the early hours of Wednesday showed images of the meeting held behind closed doors with the Aide-de-camp (ADC), Col ML Abubakar as well as the Chief of Staff to the President, Prof Ibrahim Gambari in attendance. Source By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - President Muhammadu Buhari  met with some Traditional Rulers from South West at the State House, Abuja on Friday ahead of 2019 geneeral election. The Ooni of Ife, Oba Enitan Ogunwusi, the Oba of Lagos Rilwan Akiolu amongs others were part of the Southwest traditional… January 11, 2019 In "News" ABUJA – President Muhammadu Buhari has announced the first set of appointments into his administration. The President on Sunday evening, May 31, named Mr Femi Adesina and Mal. Garba Shehu as his spokesmen. Mr. Femi Adesina will serve as Special Adviser (Media and Publicity) while Mallam Garba Shehu will be… May 31, 2015 In "News" Abuja (Sundiata Post) - President Muhammadu Buhari on Friday met behind closed door with traditional rulers from the Northern part of the country at the Presidential Villa, Abuja. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that the traditional rulers were led by the Sultan of Sokoto, Alhaji Sa’ad Abubakar and… August 23, 2019 In "Top Stories"